# ========================================
# EchoStrike: GitHub Ignore Configuration
# ========================================
# This file tells Git which files to intentionally ignore when uploading
# to the remote repository. This keeps your codebase looking extremely 
# professional, clean, and free of massive binary files or local junk!

# 1. Ignore MATLAB Crash Logs and Autosaves
*.asv
*.m~
matlab_crash_dump.*

# 2. Ignore Huge AI Models (Over 100MB)
# Note: GitHub blocks uploads over 100MB unless you use Git Large File Storage (LFS)
# Because the 'trained_svm_full_keyboard.mat' is gigantic, it's highly recommended
# to let the users train their own model, or host the .mat file on Google Drive 
# and link it in the README!
*.mat

# 3. Ignore LaTeX Compilation Junk 
# (These are generated automatically when building the PDF, no need to upload them)
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fls
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.lof
*.lot

# 4. Ignore Operating System Hidden Junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
__MACOSX/
